        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>So, my fellow Duke students, I urge you all to resist Duke Parking &amp; Transportation in any way possible. When you are met with unfair tickets and tows, I urge you to resist paying to the greatest extent possible. A member of Duke Class of 2018—whom I’ll leave unnamed for obvious reasons—graduated without ever paying his thousands of dollars owed to Duke Parking &amp; Transportation. As a result, he was handed a blank sheet rather than a diploma (although he did in fact graduate), what he considers an easy price to pay in comparison to over 50 unfair tickets.&nbsp;</p>
<p>While this Groupme is in its earlier organizing stages, I hope to collectively devise action steps to resist and reform Duke Parking &amp; Transportation. I believe in this group and this movement, because if there is anything that all Duke students can collectively get behind, it’s that Duke Parking &amp; Transportation is the <em>worst.&nbsp;</em></p>
<p><em>Bella Miller is a Trinity senior. Her column, “make Duke weird,” runs on alternate Tuesdays.</em></p>
<p><em>Correction: A previous version of this story mistakenly claimed that Blue Zone passes were priced at $423 per semester. The correct price is $423 per year. The Chronicle regrets the error.</em></p>

